{"title": "Authentication", "source": "netexec", "source_label": "NetExec Wiki", "path": "mssql-protocol/authentication", "html": "<h1 id=\"authentication\">Authentication</h1>\n<h2 id=\"testing-credentials\">Testing credentials</h2>\n<p>You can use two methods to authenticate to MSSQL: <code>windows</code> or <code>local</code> (default: <code>windows</code>). To use local auth, add the following flag <code>--local-auth</code></p>\n<h3 id=\"windows-auth\"><strong>Windows auth</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>With SMB port open</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>mssql<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.10.52<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>james<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;J@m3s_P@ssW0rd!&#39;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<ol>\n<li>With SMB port close, add the flag <code>-d DOMAIN</code></li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>mssql<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.10.52<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>james<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;J@m3s_P@ssW0rd!&#39;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-d<span class=\"w\"> </span>HTB\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Expected Results:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>MSSQL<span class=\"w\">       </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.10.52<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"m\">1433</span><span class=\"w\">   </span>MANTIS<span class=\"w\">           </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>+<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>HTB<span class=\"se\">\\j</span>ames:J@m3s_P@ssW0rd!<span class=\"w\"> </span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"local-auth\"><strong>Local auth</strong></h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>mssql<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.10.52<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>admin<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;m$$ql_S@_P@ssW0rd!&#39;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>--local-auth\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Expected Results:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>MSSQL<span class=\"w\">       </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.10.52<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"m\">1433</span><span class=\"w\">   </span>None<span class=\"w\">             </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>+<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>admin:m<span class=\"nv\">$$</span>ql_S@_P@ssW0rd!<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span>Pwn3d!<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"specify-ports\">Specify Ports</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>mssql<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.10.52<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span>admin<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;m$$ql_S@_P@ssW0rd!&#39;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>--port<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">1434</span>\n</code></pre></div>", "excerpt": "Authentication Testing credentials You can use two methods to authenticate to MSSQL: windows or local (default: windows ). To use local auth, add the following flag --local-auth Windows auth With SMB ", "tags": []}